task.summary: - Scrapped the idea of having Commandler as a generic framework, it is now made specifically for Discord to make it simpler to maintain. - Moved lots of packages around to reflect this. - Added search scopes and channel scopes to some commands. - SearchScopes now actually perform functionality. - Fixed bug where Discord objects would not be obtained correctly. - More documentation in some code, namely annotations - Fixed bug with regex to ensure it picks up command/parameters correctly. - Fixed bug with MetaParameters to ensure we accomodate MessageEvent parameters don't count as input parameters. - Made is so all param parsers, even not Discord ones just implement a single method which takes event, scope and input. (Ew but eh)

- printing stack trace on unknown error (why wasn't I before?) - Created a user parser and add this to register by default (allows the code to know how to parse a user) - Added some comments to come back to this - Fixed bug that prevented lists arguments from working properly - Fixed bug in MetaCommand that put arguments for command and parameter tags out of sync
- Added two more emotes to the boolean parser yes array
- Fixed bug in the example voice module - If user is only user in the specified channel(s) then states so - Words vary, there is one channel specified, those if multiple - Actually works XD

- Took JDA object out of sender/parser - Storing config in Confiler - Stopped creating MetaModule object multiple times per message, now just on startup - Made getter/setter for parser and sender so dev can register own parsers and senders - Added docs - Made sender and parser an interface instead of abstract class - Now made default parsers/senders optional through the auto parameter

- Renamed interfaces to start with I - No longer send message is returned object is null from handler - Validator is now object, not static - Cleaned up validators, length validator is working, limit is broken (gets mad cause casting int to long) - Created lnegth validator - Created more test methods in examplebot
